oea dispersa EGD-AAK13',53335,'Y',4764584,'bases','Pantoea is a genus of Gram-negative bacteria of the family Enterobacteriaceae, recently separated from the Enterobacter genus. This genus includes at least 20 species. Pantoea bacteria are yellow pigmented,ferment lactose, are motile, and form mucoid colonies. Besides that, some of the species show quorum sensing ability that could drive different gene expression hence controlling certain physiological activities.','heterotrophic','organotrophic','chemotrophic'),(1761774,'Burkholderia sp. B13',32008,'Y',3579262,'bases','Burkholderia bacteria are rod-shaped, motile, Gram-negative bacteria that are capable of both pathogenic characteristics and degrading PCBs. Burkholderia bacteria are both human and plant pathogens as well as environmentally important bacteria. Burkholderia fungorum strain LB400 and other closely related Burkhoderia strains are good biodegraders of polychlorinated biphenyls (PCBs) with \"unparalleled ability to destroy environmentally important PCB congeners\" (DOE). Conversely, Burkholderia pseudomallei is the causative agent of melioidosis, as disease that harms both humans and animals, as well as septicemia and pneumonia in susceptible individuals (Godoy et al. 2003). Burkholderia and related bacteria have been found at soils of all tempuratures including Arctic soil of 7oC.','heterotrophic','lithotrophic','chemotrophic');
